headline: Stock Index Futures Plunge on Fed Rate-Cut Doubts and Valuation Concerns
summary: December S&P 500 E-Mini futures (ESZ25) are down -0.97%, and December Nasdaq 100 E-Mini futures (NQZ25) are down -1.29% this morning, pointing to further losses on Wall Street as worries over stretched tech valuations persisted and investors questioned whether the Federal Reserve was still on track to cut rates in December.

headline: DIS Q3 Deep Dive: Flat Revenue and Streaming Progress Amid Market Caution
summary: Global entertainment and media company Disney (NYSE:DIS) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, with sales flat year on year at $22.46 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.11 per share was 8.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
